Class HashMap<AnyKey extends java.lang.Comparable<? super AnyKey>,AnyValue>

  • java.lang.Object
    • correlator.HashMap<AnyKey,AnyValue>
  • Type Parameters:
    E -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    MyTreeMap<AnyKey,AnyValue>

    public class HashMap<AnyKey extends java.lang.Comparable<? super AnyKey>,AnyValue>
extends java.lang.Object
implements MyTreeMap<AnyKey,AnyValue>
    This class IS the hash table, which is in the form of a HashMap. Implements a set of objects using a hash table.
    The hash table uses separate chaining to resolve collisions.
    Version:
    5.27D
    Author:
    BJP, Monika, modified by Sam Brendel

      • reAdd

        private void reAdd(HashMap.HashEntry entry)
        Helper for rehash(). Insert new value at front of linked list of HashEntry nodes.
        Connects into the new bucket list, then disconnects from the old list.
        This is a modified version of the put() method by re-linking the existing HashEntry nodes instead of creating new nodes unnecessarily. This increases efficiency of the data structure's rehash algorithm.
        Caution when using this method: before running this routine, the elementData array should be increased, AND the size field to be set to zero.
        Parameters:
        entry -
